Shin Kang-yeong, Kim Seok-joong,
Park Jun-tae

8
00:00:49,240 --> 00:00:51,710
Producer Choi Pyung-ho
Hey, listen.

9
00:00:51,780 --> 00:00:56,220
I know I'm not the usual big shot

10
00:00:56,280 --> 00:01:01,350
you're used to dealing with,
but a deal this small?

11
00:01:01,420 --> 00:01:06,190
I can manage on my own.

12
00:01:06,260 --> 00:01:09,630
I've got connection in In-sa-dong.

13
00:01:09,700 --> 00:01:11,100
In-sa-dong is great.

14
00:01:13,070 --> 00:01:16,000
Since it's my first time,

15
00:01:16,070 --> 00:01:18,200
I wasn't sure what to do.

16
00:01:19,270 --> 00:01:22,510
But I'll make sure to give you
a fat commission.

17
00:01:23,510 --> 00:01:26,070
Thank you for that.
Let's see the goods.

18
00:01:26,150 --> 00:01:27,480
Sure, sure.

19
00:01:28,150 --> 00:01:29,380
Ahh, now,

20
00:01:29,450 --> 00:01:33,680
this is called the Blue Dragon Tea Cup

21
00:01:33,760 --> 00:01:36,690
used by the Ming Dynasty nobles.

22
00:01:37,660 --> 00:01:43,290
I hear it goes
at 300 million Yen in Japan.

23
00:01:43,360 --> 00:01:44,960
- How much?
- 300 million Yen

24
00:01:46,070 --> 00:01:48,300
I own this tiny shop,

25
00:01:48,370 --> 00:01:51,500
so I go to China to get merchandise.

26
00:01:51,570 --> 00:01:55,910
Last trip to Guangzhou,
I bought this off an old Chinese man.

27
00:01:55,980 --> 00:01:59,470
Then as soon as
I get back to Korea,

28
00:01:59,550 --> 00:02:01,880
that old man gets arrested by
PSB(China's public security bureau)

29
00:02:01,950 --> 00:02:03,780
- For smuggling cultural properties
- Oh yeah?

30
00:02:03,850 --> 00:02:05,410
This old man,

31
00:02:05,490 --> 00:02:08,790
he'd run errands for
Japanese scholars during the war

32
00:02:08,860 --> 00:02:10,290
and stashed away a few artifacts.

33
00:02:10,360 --> 00:02:15,190
Not knowing its worth,
he gave it to me for nothing.

34
00:02:15,260 --> 00:02:19,600
Wow, you lucked out.

35
00:02:19,601 --> 00:02:21,201
<i><font color=yellow>Subtitle by</font></i>
<b><font color=red>Aldi Arman</font></b>

36
00:02:21,270 --> 00:02:24,300
The timing was impeccable.

37
00:02:24,370 --> 00:02:26,140
At first he didn't want to sell.

38
00:02:26,210 --> 00:02:27,000
Why?

39
00:02:27,880 --> 00:02:29,810
Some Korean dude

40
00:02:29,880 --> 00:02:32,870
begged the old man to sell
the goods to him.

41
00:02:32,950 --> 00:02:36,280
I was like, 'This is it! '
'This is the stuff.'

42
00:02:36,350 --> 00:02:37,680
So I called higher.

43
00:02:37,750 --> 00:02:39,190
- How much?
- 5 grand

44
00:02:39,950 --> 00:02:41,080
- How much?
- 5 grand

45
00:02:43,960 --> 00:02:45,980
Haha, you lucky bastard.

46
00:02:47,460 --> 00:02:48,990
High-five!

47
00:02:49,060 --> 00:02:52,290
Whoever he was,
what a poor schmuck.

48
00:02:52,370 --> 00:02:53,300
Let me shake your hand, man.

49
00:02:55,370 --> 00:02:56,600
That's me.

50
00:02:56,670 --> 00:02:57,190
What?

51
00:02:59,970 --> 00:03:03,310
That poor schmuck.
That was me, you jerk.

52
00:03:04,450 --> 00:03:05,170
Wait, wait...

53
00:03:05,250 --> 00:03:09,180
It took me over 2 months
to locate the stuff.

54
00:03:09,250 --> 00:03:12,280
Then you showed up,
and I missed it by two hours?

55
00:03:18,860 --> 00:03:19,490
What's this?

56
00:03:19,560 --> 00:03:20,790
Blue Dragon Tea Cup

57
00:03:21,360 --> 00:03:24,590
Don't you think I know that?
Where is it?

58
00:03:25,170 --> 00:03:26,190
- At home
- Where?

59
00:03:26,270 --> 00:03:28,000
At home, at home, home...

60
00:03:28,070 --> 00:03:29,700
I hid it at home.

61
00:03:29,770 --> 00:03:32,600
No one knows.
Not even my wife.

62
00:03:35,080 --> 00:03:36,100
Mr. Chang-In Ghang!

63
00:03:36,380 --> 00:03:37,780
It's the police.

64
00:03:37,850 --> 00:03:39,570
Did you call the cops, huh?

65
00:03:48,560 --> 00:03:50,150
- Are you Chang-in Ghang?
- Yes

66
00:03:50,230 --> 00:03:51,320
Chang-In Ghang,
you're under arrest

67
00:03:51,390 --> 00:03:52,830
for violation of
cultural protection act.

68
00:03:52,890 --> 00:03:53,720
Where's your warrant?

69
00:04:04,010 --> 00:04:07,770
Show me the warrant.
Where are you taking me? It hurts!

70
00:04:32,470 --> 00:04:33,400
Call it in.

71
00:04:35,070 --> 00:04:36,700
Let's go.

72
00:05:03,870 --> 00:05:05,200
Check the roof, go!

73
00:05:05,870 --> 00:05:08,500
Man down. Man down.

74
00:05:08,570 --> 00:05:10,540
Male, mid-30s. John Doe.

75
00:05:10,610 --> 00:05:13,300
Fell from the roof top
during the arrest.

76
00:05:39,470 --> 00:05:43,100
Villain and Widow

77
00:05:50,280 --> 00:05:53,480
You're in 80 km/h zone.

78
00:05:53,550 --> 00:05:55,980
Please slow down.

79
00:05:56,750 --> 00:05:58,480
Turn it down!

80
00:06:09,060 --> 00:06:12,190
Alarm disabled. Welcome.

81
00:06:18,370 --> 00:06:20,000
I'm never going to see
the grandparents again,

82
00:06:20,070 --> 00:06:21,510
not even for the holidays.

83
00:06:21,580 --> 00:06:23,770
I don't know why we keep going.
Dad's not around anymore.

84
00:06:23,850 --> 00:06:24,970
That's enough.

85
00:06:39,460 --> 00:06:42,290
You have to weed
the yard after it rains...

86
00:06:47,570 --> 00:06:51,100
Your home is now secured.

87
00:06:53,880 --> 00:06:56,210
Your yard's full of weed.

88
00:06:57,850 --> 00:06:58,370
What?

89
00:06:58,450 --> 00:07:01,970
You need to weed it out
to grow something.

90
00:07:02,050 --> 00:07:03,780
We don't grow anything anymore.

91
00:07:03,850 --> 00:07:06,580
We buy everything from the store
with pesticide all over them.

92
00:07:09,860 --> 00:07:11,980
Why do I even bother...

93
00:07:27,180 --> 00:07:30,630
Room Available to Rent

94
00:07:39,820 --> 00:07:43,880
So, Mr. Ghang's never seen
the goods in person...

95
00:07:43,960 --> 00:07:47,860
The Chinese who sold the stuff
got caught by PSB for smuggling.

96
00:07:47,930 --> 00:07:49,990
It was just bad timing.

97
00:07:50,870 --> 00:07:53,800
Didn't you guys look into it?

98
00:07:53,870 --> 00:07:55,390
Yeah, we figured out
what's going on.

99
00:07:55,470 --> 00:07:56,800
Well, then.

100
00:07:56,870 --> 00:07:59,400
We just bring you the goods,
get it appraised,

101
00:07:59,870 --> 00:08:01,210
And if it is good, you pay us.

102
00:08:01,980 --> 00:08:04,380
If it isn't, you don't.
What's the big deal?

103
00:08:04,450 --> 00:08:08,210
I believe my boss is entitled
to an explanation.

104
00:08:08,280 --> 00:08:09,480
Entitled?

105
00:08:11,750 --> 00:08:15,880
Not that I doubt
your abilities, Mr. Ghang

106
00:08:17,860 --> 00:08:20,790
I just want to make sure
if you need any help,

107
00:08:20,860 --> 00:08:22,590
say, more people

108
00:08:22,660 --> 00:08:24,600
No, I don't need more people.

109
00:08:24,670 --> 00:08:29,330
Well, if there aren't any questions,
we'll see ourselves out.

110
00:08:39,450 --> 00:08:42,880
He's paying us 2 million dollars.
Was it so hard to be nice?

111
00:08:43,450 --> 00:08:45,080
Is he really the president
of this company?

112
00:08:45,150 --> 00:08:46,080
What do you mean?

113
00:08:46,850 --> 00:08:49,080
Why is he handling things directly?

114
00:08:49,160 --> 00:08:50,680
Is that a problem?

115
00:08:50,760 --> 00:08:53,390
He needs to delegate to his people.

116
00:08:53,960 --> 00:08:56,290
He's too exposed from the start.

117
00:09:01,270 --> 00:09:03,400
He's just really desperate.

118
00:09:03,470 --> 00:09:06,300
He's got a gallery
at the headquarters.

119
00:09:06,810 --> 00:09:09,210
He took 10 million from arts budget
behind his father's back

120
00:09:09,280 --> 00:09:11,470
for money laundering and
lost everything in bad investment.

121
00:09:11,550 --> 00:09:14,380
So he needs something
to make up for it, right away.

122
00:09:15,050 --> 00:09:16,280
Pardon me.

123
00:09:17,620 --> 00:09:18,980
My name is Mr. Song.

124
00:09:19,450 --> 00:09:22,080
If you need anything,
please call me any time.

125
00:09:33,570 --> 00:09:35,090
Who's the midget?

126
00:09:35,670 --> 00:09:37,300
Some punk.

127
00:09:37,370 --> 00:09:39,900
Mr. Ha takes him around
as his bodyguard.

128
00:09:39,970 --> 00:09:43,210
Show off at the clubs, you know.

129
00:09:44,750 --> 00:09:46,580
Real mature.

130
00:09:47,750 --> 00:09:50,680
Don't underestimate
residential security system.

131
00:09:51,150 --> 00:09:53,590
You can go in and out
of a jewelry shop in a minute,

132
00:09:53,650 --> 00:09:55,990
but this takes at least 3 to 4 days.

133
00:09:56,460 --> 00:09:59,290
You look into the security company.

134
00:09:59,990 --> 00:10:02,390
Who's got time to research all that?

135
00:10:02,460 --> 00:10:04,590
Delaying will upset Mr. Ha.

136
00:10:04,670 --> 00:10:08,190
Why should I care,
he hasn't paid me up front.

137
00:10:08,270 --> 00:10:11,900
Can't you just tie them up
and go through the house?

138
00:10:11,970 --> 00:10:13,200
It's only a woman and her daughter.

139
00:10:15,880 --> 00:10:17,280
Sure, because when I untie them,

140
00:10:17,350 --> 00:10:22,150
she'll say 'Thank you'.
Just like that. Sure.

141
00:10:22,220 --> 00:10:24,980
Just make sure they won't
want to call the cops.

142
00:10:25,050 --> 00:10:26,280
How do I do that?

143
00:10:26,350 --> 00:10:29,790
- You know how.
- Seriously, how?

144
00:10:29,860 --> 00:10:32,490
You know... just...

145
00:10:32,560 --> 00:10:33,890
Must I say it out loud?

146
00:10:33,960 --> 00:10:35,790
What if it goes bad?

147
00:10:35,860 --> 00:10:38,300
I'd have to rot in jail
for another 5~6 years.

148
00:10:39,070 --> 00:10:43,200
Chang-In, life is all about
preparing for the future.

149
00:10:43,270 --> 00:10:45,200
That requires money.

150
00:10:46,070 --> 00:10:47,800
This is my last chance.

151
00:10:47,880 --> 00:10:50,000
I'm old.

152
00:10:50,650 --> 00:10:53,670
This guy is paying us
2 million at once. In cash!

153
00:10:53,750 --> 00:10:54,980
Opportunities like this
don't come again.

154
00:10:56,550 --> 00:10:59,880
This is literally, 'show me the money'.
'Show me the money! '

155
00:11:09,960 --> 00:11:12,590
How about just 3 grand?

156
00:11:17,570 --> 00:11:20,100
It must be hard for you, too.

157
00:11:26,750 --> 00:11:30,580
Anyone interested in renting
my spare room upstairs?

158
00:11:30,650 --> 00:11:32,380
That's not an easy sale.

159
00:11:32,450 --> 00:11:35,180
It's just a room, in someone's home.

160
00:11:35,260 --> 00:11:39,280
Don't young people look for studios?

161
00:11:39,360 --> 00:11:42,390
Why would kids want to live
in your neighborhood?

162
00:11:42,460 --> 00:11:43,690
They want to live in the city.

163
00:11:58,180 --> 00:12:00,980
Mom, I want to get my eyes done.

164
00:12:05,150 --> 00:12:09,180
Mom, please? Can I?

165
00:12:09,660 --> 00:12:11,090
Please?

166
00:12:11,160 --> 00:12:13,090
Your eyes are just fine.

167
00:12:14,160 --> 00:12:15,890
You're not ugly.

168
00:12:15,960 --> 00:12:17,690
I am ugly.

169
00:12:17,770 --> 00:12:19,490
No wonder I can't get any parts.

170
00:12:19,570 --> 00:12:22,900
You didn't fail your auditions
because you're ugly.

171
00:12:22,970 --> 00:12:25,400
It's because you can't act.

172
00:12:25,470 --> 00:12:27,410
I want cosmetic surgery!

173
00:12:27,480 --> 00:12:28,600
I have no money.

174
00:12:28,680 --> 00:12:30,870
You always say that.
Come on, mom.

175
00:12:30,950 --> 00:12:33,380
Please? Just once?!

176
00:12:33,450 --> 00:12:34,470
- I got no money. None.
- Surgery!

177
00:12:34,550 --> 00:12:37,480
No money. No money.
Your mom never has any.

178
00:13:31,870 --> 00:13:33,600
Who is it?

179
00:13:33,670 --> 00:13:35,510
I'm here to check out your room.

180
00:13:38,850 --> 00:13:40,970
This room is really perfect
for just one person.

181
00:13:44,290 --> 00:13:47,690
I don't mean to be rude,
but what kind of work do you do?

182
00:13:49,890 --> 00:13:52,190
What do I look like I do?

183
00:13:55,300 --> 00:13:58,490
Since you came all the way
out here for a room,

184
00:13:59,600 --> 00:14:03,500
You probably need
a quiet work space

185
00:14:05,840 --> 00:14:09,300
You're right. I'm a writer.

186
00:14:11,150 --> 00:14:13,480
I see, what kind of writer?

187
00:14:15,750 --> 00:14:17,680
I write trashy comments
on the Internet.

188
00:14:18,950 --> 00:14:19,680
Excuse me?

189
00:14:22,060 --> 00:14:23,080
I'm kidding.

190
00:14:24,360 --> 00:14:25,880
I write novels.

191
00:14:26,460 --> 00:14:30,900
Oh, you're an author.

192
00:14:30,970 --> 00:14:32,990
No, not a big author.

193
00:14:33,670 --> 00:14:35,690
I'm a bit peculiar.

194
00:14:35,770 --> 00:14:39,000
I just can't write in hotel rooms,

195
00:14:39,070 --> 00:14:40,900
and the city is too loud.

196
00:14:41,480 --> 00:14:43,500
This neighborhood is really quiet.

197
00:14:43,580 --> 00:14:44,370
Oh yeah?

198
00:14:44,950 --> 00:14:48,380
Well, the room seems just fine.

199
00:14:48,950 --> 00:14:51,470
Could I trouble you for a cup of tea?

200
00:15:03,260 --> 00:15:08,200
How long does it take to write?

201
00:15:08,270 --> 00:15:11,900
Well, it depends on the book.

202
00:15:12,570 --> 00:15:16,410
This one,
I think maybe about a month.

203
00:15:16,480 --> 00:15:18,570
So you're looking
for short-term lease.

204
00:15:18,650 --> 00:15:20,080
Yes, I am.

205
00:15:26,450 --> 00:15:29,080
Wow, you have a nice view.

206
00:15:29,160 --> 00:15:31,090
Hmm? Yeah.

207
00:15:31,160 --> 00:15:33,590
How are the neighbors?

208
00:15:33,660 --> 00:15:35,560
Do they visit each other often?

209
00:15:35,630 --> 00:15:36,620
No, not really.

210
00:15:36,700 --> 00:15:39,390
They're mostly old folks
being concerned.

211
00:15:39,470 --> 00:15:39,990
Here's your tea.

212
00:15:40,070 --> 00:15:41,590
Thank you.

213
00:15:47,070 --> 00:15:49,600
Hmm, this tea is Tie Guan Yin.

214
00:15:49,780 --> 00:15:52,940
You must know a lot about tea.

215
00:15:53,050 --> 00:15:56,380
Not at all.
I just enjoy tea from time to time.

216
00:15:56,950 --> 00:15:59,980
- By the way, .
- Yes?

217
00:16:00,850 --> 00:16:04,290
It's customary to charge
two months' rent upfront.

218
00:16:04,360 --> 00:16:06,990
One month rent is
impossible to find, anywhere.

219
00:16:09,160 --> 00:16:11,190
You're home.
How was school?

220
00:16:12,470 --> 00:16:13,090
What's this?

221
00:16:13,970 --> 00:16:15,990
Where are your manners?

222
00:16:18,870 --> 00:16:20,100
- I'm really sorry. Excuse me.
- Sure.

223
00:16:38,630 --> 00:16:40,390
What is the matter with you?

224
00:16:40,460 --> 00:16:41,190
Who is he?

225
00:16:41,260 --> 00:16:43,700
He's here to see the room.

226
00:16:43,760 --> 00:16:47,600
That guy? Alone?
Are you crazy?

227
00:16:48,170 --> 00:16:50,000
Who are you calling crazy?

228
00:16:50,070 --> 00:16:54,600
Can't you tell?
He's a writer. A gentleman.

229
00:16:54,680 --> 00:16:55,800
No way.

230
00:16:55,880 --> 00:16:57,840
Why not?

231
00:16:57,910 --> 00:17:00,470
Where else will we
get money from, huh?

232
00:17:00,550 --> 00:17:02,570
I can't exactly afford to
turn him down.

233
00:17:02,650 --> 00:17:04,580
Well, I don't like him.
Send him back.

234
00:17:04,650 --> 00:17:05,880
Send him where? Keep it down.

235
00:17:05,950 --> 00:17:06,890
I said no.

236
00:17:06,950 --> 00:17:09,080
He'll hear you.
Be quiet, Seong-Ah Hahm!

237
00:17:09,160 --> 00:17:09,990
Get him out, now!

238
00:17:10,060 --> 00:17:11,680
He stays.
Settle down!

239
00:17:11,760 --> 00:17:12,780
I don't like him.

240
00:17:12,860 --> 00:17:14,190
Be quiet, Seong-Ah Hahm! Hush!

241
00:17:14,260 --> 00:17:15,290
I don't like him!

242
00:17:17,260 --> 00:17:18,090
I said be quiet!

243
00:17:23,970 --> 00:17:27,600
Oh, you really don't have much stuff.

244
00:17:27,670 --> 00:17:31,670
All a writer needs are his laptop
and a desk. What else?

245
00:17:44,160 --> 00:17:45,180
You're annoying.

246
00:17:45,260 --> 00:17:47,890
Who rents a room to steal
a piece of china?

247
00:17:47,960 --> 00:17:52,090
This is the only way to discretely
look for it without the fuss.

248
00:17:52,170 --> 00:17:55,690
I can't afford to get in trouble
by tying up those girls.

249
00:17:57,670 --> 00:17:59,610
Do you want the table here?

250
00:18:02,780 --> 00:18:03,770
Oh, you're here.

251
00:18:06,250 --> 00:18:08,870
Shouldn't we sign
a lease or something?

252
00:18:09,250 --> 00:18:10,180
Should I ask the realtor?

253
00:18:10,250 --> 00:18:12,680
Oh, no problem.
I don't care if we do.

254
00:18:13,490 --> 00:18:16,790
I just don't want to waste
any money on brokerage fees.

255
00:18:17,460 --> 00:18:18,980
I'm only here for two months.

256
00:18:20,860 --> 00:18:22,800
Hey, you must be uncomfortable.

257
00:18:22,860 --> 00:18:24,300
I should show you some ID.

258
00:18:24,360 --> 00:18:26,590
Oh no.
I didn't mean it like that.

259
00:18:26,670 --> 00:18:28,690
No, no. We should be clear on this.

260
00:18:30,770 --> 00:18:35,230
My publisher says even authors
need business cards nowadays.

261
00:18:35,310 --> 00:18:36,830
Hyeong-Gook Park, Author
Mangook Publishing

262
00:18:39,350 --> 00:18:41,970
- Well, make yourself at home.
- Okay.

263
00:18:44,850 --> 00:18:46,980
- See you later.
- Bye.

264
00:19:20,750 --> 00:19:24,090
Did you get a tenant?
I saw a man.

265
00:19:24,160 --> 00:19:27,590
Yes, I rented out the room upstairs.

266
00:19:27,660 --> 00:19:30,890
A man moved into a house of two girls.

267
00:19:30,960 --> 00:19:33,690
He's a writer.
He writes novels.

268
00:19:33,770 --> 00:19:39,300
A man who's a writer
moved into a house of two girls.

269
00:19:57,660 --> 00:20:00,680
What's up?

270
00:20:00,760 --> 00:20:03,490
- Um, sir.
- Yes?

271
00:20:03,560 --> 00:20:07,400
- I'm really sorry, but...
- Yeah?

272
00:20:08,870 --> 00:20:11,200
- I've been thinking and...
- Well, ma'am,

273
00:20:11,270 --> 00:20:15,300
I paid you
two months' rent upfront, right?

274
00:20:15,380 --> 00:20:17,470
Yes, two months.

275
00:20:17,540 --> 00:20:20,270
Then I have the right to live here
for two months, right?

276
00:20:20,350 --> 00:20:21,680
Why, of course...

277
00:20:25,050 --> 00:20:26,490
Did you want to say something?

278
00:20:26,550 --> 00:20:29,580
Um, would you like
some dinner?

279
00:20:29,660 --> 00:20:34,290
I only eat fruits when I write.

280
00:20:35,060 --> 00:20:37,690
- How about some tea?
- No thank you.

281
00:20:37,760 --> 00:20:40,700
Well, you should get some rest then.

282
00:20:40,770 --> 00:20:41,700
Okay, then.

283
00:20:44,770 --> 00:20:45,700
Good night.

284
00:20:51,650 --> 00:20:52,770
Who's she think she's dealing with?

285
00:21:22,480 --> 00:21:23,600
I love you.

286
00:21:34,350 --> 00:21:35,290
Seong-Ah Hahm!

287
00:21:45,770 --> 00:21:48,600
- Oh my...
- He's so hot, isn't he?

288
00:21:49,040 --> 00:21:50,800
Look at you pretending
like you don't know.

289
00:21:50,870 --> 00:21:52,400
I really don't know.

290
00:21:52,470 --> 00:21:54,600
- You really don't know?
- I don't.

291
00:21:54,680 --> 00:21:58,170
- You went karaoke-ing that time.
- How would I know that?

292
00:21:58,250 --> 00:21:59,270
Then she's all mine.

293
00:22:25,970 --> 00:22:29,310
Let's see who wins this battle.

294
00:22:32,850 --> 00:22:36,080
- You're home early.
- Yeah

295
00:22:36,950 --> 00:22:40,280
It isn't much, but this is Bolay tea.

296
00:22:40,350 --> 00:22:42,290
I thought you might
appreciate gourmet tea.

297
00:22:43,160 --> 00:22:45,990
Oh, thank you.

298
00:22:46,060 --> 00:22:47,890
I haven't tried it yet...

299
00:22:51,160 --> 00:22:53,500
I haven't had that tea, yet.

300
00:22:56,670 --> 00:22:58,600
Oh, would you like some tea?

301
00:22:58,670 --> 00:23:01,200
No, you don't have to.

302
00:23:01,270 --> 00:23:02,210
Thank you.

303
00:23:07,350 --> 00:23:08,370
- Give me a minute.
- Sure.

304
00:23:20,760 --> 00:23:23,790
You have a lot of plants here.

305
00:23:24,660 --> 00:23:25,490
Yeah.

306
00:23:25,570 --> 00:23:29,300
It's interesting to put them
on the steps like this.

307
00:23:35,280 --> 00:23:38,770
- By the way, sir.
- Yes?

308
00:23:38,850 --> 00:23:40,680
What kind of story are you writing?

309
00:23:41,550 --> 00:23:44,070
Well, that's...

310
00:23:48,560 --> 00:23:53,390
What I'm writing is...
about a woman.

311
00:23:55,760 --> 00:24:01,200
Once she had many dreams.
She was pretty.

312
00:24:02,570 --> 00:24:05,090
But one day, she looked back

313
00:24:05,170 --> 00:24:08,900
and those days were gone.

314
00:24:09,680 --> 00:24:13,980
This isn't the life she wanted.

315
00:24:14,050 --> 00:24:17,680
She's like my sister,
crying in front of a mirror.

316
00:24:19,450 --> 00:24:20,890
That's what I'm working on.

317
00:24:23,260 --> 00:24:25,780
Speaking of,

318
00:24:26,360 --> 00:24:29,290
Could I come down
to interview you sometimes?

319
00:24:31,470 --> 00:24:32,690
Me?

320
00:24:32,770 --> 00:24:35,430
Yes.

321
00:24:35,500 --> 00:24:39,800
I think you're similar
to the character in my novel.

322
00:24:39,870 --> 00:24:44,170
Well, I don't have much of a story.

323
00:24:44,740 --> 00:24:46,180
No, no.

324
00:24:47,450 --> 00:24:51,980
Everyone is the main character
in their life story.

325
00:24:52,450 --> 00:24:59,380
Oh that. I put up bricks
and plastered with cement.

326
00:24:59,460 --> 00:25:03,090
- Cement?
- Yeah.

327
00:25:06,170 --> 00:25:10,190
You plastered the wall with cement?

328
00:25:10,270 --> 00:25:12,900
Yeah, so it's quiet.

329
00:25:25,750 --> 00:25:28,780
- The whole wall?
- Yes, completely.

330
00:25:31,160 --> 00:25:33,490
- Have a seat, sir.
- Okay.

331
00:25:39,170 --> 00:25:41,190
- Well, sir.
- Yes?

332
00:25:41,270 --> 00:25:44,400
I'd hate to bring this up again,

333
00:25:44,470 --> 00:25:46,410
but I asked around and

334
00:25:46,470 --> 00:25:49,600
even a short-term tenant

335
00:25:49,680 --> 00:25:52,870
should pay a deposit.

336
00:25:52,950 --> 00:25:54,880
- Really?
- Yes.

337
00:25:56,550 --> 00:25:58,880
If you can't come up
with the deposit right away,

338
00:25:58,950 --> 00:26:02,580
maybe you can pay more rent?

339
00:26:02,660 --> 00:26:06,390
Isn't it like 100 dollars more
for every 10 grand?

340
00:26:07,860 --> 00:26:12,090
Well, you're right.
I will get it to you.

341
00:26:12,170 --> 00:26:14,400
Good. I will write up the lease.

342
00:26:15,970 --> 00:26:19,500
I thought I told you
I don't need the lease.

343
00:26:23,480 --> 00:26:24,970
Hey, Seong-Ah.

344
00:26:25,050 --> 00:26:26,480
Sorry about her.

345
00:26:27,450 --> 00:26:30,680
She's going through puberty.

346
00:26:30,750 --> 00:26:31,480
No worries.

347
00:26:35,560 --> 00:26:37,390
Not like it's the first time
she's being rude.

348
00:26:37,860 --> 00:26:40,190
Where did you learn to behave
like this, in front of an elder?

349
00:26:40,260 --> 00:26:41,590
How would that make me look?

350
00:26:41,660 --> 00:26:43,090
He's hanging out here now?

351
00:26:43,160 --> 00:26:46,000
Don't overreact.
He's just having tea.

352
00:26:46,070 --> 00:26:48,190
I hate him. Make him leave.

353
00:26:48,270 --> 00:26:50,900
Why are you acting so weird?

354
00:26:50,970 --> 00:26:52,700
He must feel so uncomfortable.

355
00:26:52,770 --> 00:26:54,760
Why are you treating him
like he's fecal matter?

356
00:26:54,840 --> 00:26:56,900
How nice, comparing me to shit.

357
00:26:56,980 --> 00:26:59,570
Why can't you be
considerate of others?

358
00:26:59,650 --> 00:27:01,270
Whatever.
I hate him. Send him home.

359
00:27:01,350 --> 00:27:03,680
How come you hate
so many things, huh?

360
00:27:39,450 --> 00:27:42,180
Hey, you're still up studying.

361
00:27:44,160 --> 00:27:47,790
I just came out for some air.
I couldn't write.

362
00:27:52,070 --> 00:27:53,590
Alright then.

363
00:27:54,970 --> 00:27:58,500
Here, buy yourself a book.

364
00:28:05,850 --> 00:28:07,970
No discipline around here, huh?

365
00:28:10,180 --> 00:28:12,210
What do you mean,
you can't get through the stairs?

366
00:28:12,590 --> 00:28:14,920
She brick-walled it and
plastered cement all over.

367
00:28:14,990 --> 00:28:16,080
And you moved in without
even checking that out?

368
00:28:16,620 --> 00:28:18,760
Don't get upset.
I'll take care of it.

369
00:28:18,760 --> 00:28:21,190
We assured them
it'll only take 3~4 days.

370
00:28:21,260 --> 00:28:23,590
Tell them to wait a few.

371
00:28:23,660 --> 00:28:25,600
And send me money for the deposit.

372
00:28:30,870 --> 00:28:34,900
Wow, it's really nice in here.

373
00:28:35,880 --> 00:28:38,170
Did you decorate it yourself?

374
00:28:38,240 --> 00:28:40,180
With my husband.

375
00:28:41,150 --> 00:28:42,980
Here. What you asked.

376
00:28:44,450 --> 00:28:49,480
By the way, I need to use
the Internet for research,

377
00:28:49,560 --> 00:28:51,390
but I don't get Internet connection
from my room.

378
00:28:51,460 --> 00:28:55,090
Could I use the computer downstairs?

379
00:28:55,160 --> 00:28:57,190
Well, the computer...

380
00:28:57,760 --> 00:28:59,100
The additional deposit.
Two months worth.

381
00:28:59,170 --> 00:29:01,190
Thank you.

382
00:29:01,270 --> 00:29:05,400
I'll only need
to use it for 3~4 days.

383
00:29:06,170 --> 00:29:09,110
That's not going to work.

384
00:29:09,180 --> 00:29:09,800
What?

385
00:29:10,840 --> 00:29:14,080
It doesn't look good if you're
downstairs by yourself during the day.

386
00:29:14,150 --> 00:29:18,680
Well, I'll be quiet during the day.
Who's going to see me?

387
00:29:19,950 --> 00:29:24,190
There used to be some unique items
here when the husband was around.

388
00:29:26,560 --> 00:29:29,290
The husband died
in a unique fashion last year.

389
00:29:29,860 --> 00:29:32,090
Did I say something wrong?

390
00:29:32,170 --> 00:29:34,790
It's okay.
You didn't kill him.

391
00:29:34,870 --> 00:29:38,500
If it's Internet fee,
I will pay you.

392
00:29:39,370 --> 00:29:41,100
I even gave you the deposit.

393
00:29:42,480 --> 00:29:44,570
Wait a minute.

394
00:29:44,640 --> 00:29:47,370
I rightfully deserved that deposit.

395
00:29:47,450 --> 00:29:50,080
Come on.

396
00:29:50,650 --> 00:29:52,980
Seriously, I only need
a month to finish writing,

397
00:29:53,050 --> 00:29:55,180
but I paid rent for two months.

398
00:29:55,260 --> 00:29:58,380
Then you asked for more deposit,
which I paid.

399
00:29:58,460 --> 00:30:01,390
Still, you won't
let me use the Internet?

400
00:30:01,460 --> 00:30:04,090
Nowhere in this country
can you rent a room for one month,

401
00:30:04,160 --> 00:30:05,690
not unless it's a motel.

402
00:30:05,770 --> 00:30:08,200
There's a cyber cafe down the street.

403
00:30:08,270 --> 00:30:11,000
How can a writer work in a cyber cafe?

404
00:30:11,070 --> 00:30:13,500
There are loud kids,
playing games.

405
00:30:13,570 --> 00:30:15,600
Why are you yelling at me?

406
00:30:15,680 --> 00:30:17,770
When did I yell?

407
00:30:17,840 --> 00:30:19,180
It's just the Internet.

408
00:30:19,250 --> 00:30:20,970
Just go to the cyber cafe, go!

409
00:30:45,970 --> 00:30:47,100
It's been a while.

410
00:30:48,070 --> 00:30:49,600
You must be out of your prescription.

411
00:30:49,680 --> 00:30:51,080
It must be half-life.

412
00:30:52,050 --> 00:30:54,780
The pills are not working anymore.

413
00:30:55,450 --> 00:30:57,280
You still can't sleep
without drinking?

414
00:30:59,350 --> 00:31:02,690
But I don't drink hard liquor.

415
00:31:03,560 --> 00:31:05,490
I only drink wine or beer.

416
00:31:05,560 --> 00:31:07,390
It doesn't matter what kind
of alcohol you drink.

417
00:31:07,460 --> 00:31:10,400
I told you many times.
Drinking every night isn't good for you.

418
00:31:10,460 --> 00:31:12,590
Do you still often get irritated?

419
00:31:12,670 --> 00:31:18,190
But, that's not depression.

420
00:31:18,270 --> 00:31:23,570
Getting angry with people
around you, saying things you regret.

421
00:31:23,640 --> 00:31:26,170
That can also cause you
to feel depressed.

422
00:31:27,580 --> 00:31:32,070
Doctor, please.
Stop staring at me like that.

423
00:31:32,150 --> 00:31:32,550
What?

424
00:31:32,620 --> 00:31:35,380
It feels like your eyes are
shooting sharp knives at me.

425
00:31:35,460 --> 00:31:37,580
I know it's rude of me to say,
but your eyes don't look right.

426
00:31:37,660 --> 00:31:39,680
Just when I'm ready
to share with you,

427
00:31:39,760 --> 00:31:42,690
I see your eyes and shut up.

428
00:31:42,760 --> 00:31:44,290
I was just walking by and saw,

429
00:31:44,360 --> 00:31:46,390
Jeong-Shim Kim, Psychiatrist

430
00:31:46,470 --> 00:31:47,990
and thought you were
a female doctor.

431
00:31:48,070 --> 00:31:49,800
What kind of man
has a name Jeong-Shim?

432
00:31:51,770 --> 00:31:53,200
Honestly, if you were a woman,

433
00:31:53,270 --> 00:31:54,900
Maybe I'd feel
more comfortable sharing.

434
00:31:54,970 --> 00:31:56,410
But when I'm with you,

435
00:31:56,480 --> 00:31:59,170
I feel like a kid getting
scorned by a teacher.

436
00:31:59,250 --> 00:32:01,180
Why can't you make
your patient feel at ease?

437
00:32:01,250 --> 00:32:04,580
All you do is criticize
and pick me apart.

438
00:32:05,250 --> 00:32:07,080
It's not too late.

439
00:32:07,950 --> 00:32:11,190
Feel free to go else where.
To a female doctor.

440
00:32:11,260 --> 00:32:14,780
And my apologies
my family named me a girly name.

441
00:32:15,360 --> 00:32:16,890
Do you angry?

442
00:32:20,200 --> 00:32:23,500
Next time, try this doctor.

443
00:32:23,970 --> 00:32:25,490
She is really feminine.

444
00:32:33,450 --> 00:32:34,780
Got Milk? Girl Seong-Ah Hahm Today

445
00:32:47,960 --> 00:32:49,790
Best Comment:
Did you put shit in your milk?

446
00:32:52,670 --> 00:32:55,000
Mom, the kids are...

447
00:32:58,370 --> 00:32:59,100
Yeah?

448
00:33:03,680 --> 00:33:05,370
Nothing. Goodnight.

449
00:33:05,450 --> 00:33:06,470
Go to sleep.

450
00:33:21,060 --> 00:33:25,590
What are you doing here?
What if someone sees you?

451
00:33:25,670 --> 00:33:29,900
How is your writing coming along?

452
00:33:29,970 --> 00:33:33,700
How can I write,
when I can't use the Internet?

453
00:33:42,350 --> 00:33:45,480
- Hey, Mister
- Huh?

454
00:33:46,050 --> 00:33:49,080
- Can you buy me a drink?
- What?

455
00:33:49,160 --> 00:33:51,490
What is your name?

456
00:33:52,890 --> 00:33:55,090
Oh, it's Yeon-Joo.
Yeon-Joo Choi.

457
00:33:57,300 --> 00:34:02,200
Yeon-Joo Choi...
Yeon as in "become" and Joo as in "jewel"

458
00:34:02,270 --> 00:34:03,290
Joo as in "house"

459
00:34:05,170 --> 00:34:08,500
Joo as in "house"
because you own the house.

460
00:34:10,380 --> 00:34:11,470
You know, sir.

461
00:34:14,450 --> 00:34:18,980
Do you really think my story
can be used for your book?

462
00:34:20,250 --> 00:34:21,580
Sure.

463
00:34:21,650 --> 00:34:26,180
I'm not good at logically telling

464
00:34:26,260 --> 00:34:29,990
a story about my circumstances.

465
00:34:30,060 --> 00:34:33,790
No, no, no. I can totally relate.

466
00:34:34,970 --> 00:34:37,800
I haven't said anything, yet.

467
00:34:39,870 --> 00:34:41,100
Desperation.

468
00:34:41,970 --> 00:34:46,070
Something that desperately
asks me to hear you out.

469
00:34:46,150 --> 00:34:49,270
That's hit my imagination.

470
00:34:49,350 --> 00:34:50,580
Hit you?

471
00:34:52,850 --> 00:34:53,780
When did I hit you?

472
00:34:53,850 --> 00:34:58,480
Listen, lady.
You must be my muse.

473
00:34:58,560 --> 00:35:02,090
I will repay you with a great story.

474
00:35:02,160 --> 00:35:04,290
Excuse me.
I have to go to the restroom.

475
00:35:04,960 --> 00:35:05,790
Okay.

476
00:35:19,150 --> 00:35:20,770
How long to copy this?

477
00:35:20,850 --> 00:35:22,080
I'll try to be back by dawn.

478
00:35:22,150 --> 00:35:23,380
That's too late.

479
00:35:23,450 --> 00:35:26,080
Just keep her occupied.
You're good at it.

480
00:35:33,260 --> 00:35:36,290
I got married
straight out of high school.

481
00:35:36,360 --> 00:35:37,390
No wonder...

482
00:35:38,260 --> 00:35:41,600
I thought it was weird
you have a kid in junior high.

483
00:35:44,970 --> 00:35:46,300
Thirty-five.

484
00:35:47,670 --> 00:35:49,900
I'm an oldie in her mid-thirties.

485
00:35:50,940 --> 00:35:52,880
So weird.

486
00:35:52,950 --> 00:35:55,510
Koreans just love it when you say
they look a year or two younger.

487
00:35:55,580 --> 00:35:57,570
If they love looking younger so much,

488
00:35:57,650 --> 00:35:59,580
let's count our age the exact way,

489
00:35:59,650 --> 00:36:03,380
like they do in European Union.

490
00:36:03,460 --> 00:36:06,690
Then you can be
in your early thirties.

491
00:36:06,760 --> 00:36:08,390
Early thirties.

492
00:36:08,460 --> 00:36:09,890
Feels different, right?

493
00:36:12,060 --> 00:36:14,000
You're really good with words.

494
00:36:14,070 --> 00:36:16,560
You know, us writers,
we keep a hundred,

495
00:36:16,640 --> 00:36:23,300
no thousands of thoughts
in our heads to get one thing out.

496
00:36:25,410 --> 00:36:27,570
- You're like a con artist.
- What?

497
00:36:28,550 --> 00:36:29,280
Nothing.

498
00:36:33,350 --> 00:36:35,290
Hey, here. One more.

499
00:36:38,660 --> 00:36:41,790
It goes in,
but keeps getting errors.

500
00:36:42,660 --> 00:36:44,290
I know, but I'm in a hurry.

501
00:36:45,060 --> 00:36:46,090
What, depression?

502
00:36:46,770 --> 00:36:49,390
At first, I couldn't figure out
what I was feeling.

503
00:36:51,170 --> 00:36:54,610
It was all so sudden, new emotions.
I was going crazy.

504
00:36:54,670 --> 00:36:58,270
I know. Steel doesn't get
rusty overnight.

505
00:36:59,150 --> 00:37:02,880
It takes a lot of time,
being exposed to sun,

506
00:37:02,950 --> 00:37:06,890
and getting rusty by rain.

507
00:37:08,420 --> 00:37:13,590
Sometimes, even washing dishes
seems like an impossible task.

508
00:37:13,660 --> 00:37:16,790
Fatigue. Simple routine life.

509
00:37:16,860 --> 00:37:22,100
It's easy for homemakers
to get depression.

510
00:37:22,170 --> 00:37:23,660
Work out.

511
00:37:23,740 --> 00:37:25,200
Before going to bed,

512
00:37:25,270 --> 00:37:27,100
if you run an hour on the treadmill,

513
00:37:27,170 --> 00:37:29,700
you'll fall asleep like a baby.

514
00:37:30,380 --> 00:37:32,470
I thought this was my interview.

515
00:37:32,550 --> 00:37:35,570
Shouldn't you be listening to me?
Stop interrupting.

516
00:37:37,050 --> 00:37:39,380
I was just trying to help.

517
00:37:39,450 --> 00:37:40,580
Who asked you to help?

518
00:37:43,390 --> 00:37:44,690
Since you're a writer,

519
00:37:44,760 --> 00:37:47,590
I thought you'd be a good listener

520
00:37:47,660 --> 00:37:50,290
