We cannot cross this line,
understand?

1044
01:25:46,240 --> 01:25:47,290
Yes, sir!

1045
01:25:49,970 --> 01:25:53,670
You got until tomorrow.
No point in running.

1046
01:25:54,380 --> 01:25:58,400
Catching a loud-mouth,
old rat in this country...

1047
01:25:58,480 --> 01:25:59,970
easy as pie.

1048
01:26:36,850 --> 01:26:40,580
Where is it?
Where did you hide it?

1049
01:27:23,270 --> 01:27:24,100
What are you doing?

1050
01:27:25,470 --> 01:27:26,490
I'm trying to kill myself.

1051
01:27:31,940 --> 01:27:34,380
You can't die like that.

1052
01:27:35,450 --> 01:27:37,680
Then how can I die?

1053
01:27:38,550 --> 01:27:41,070
What have you got to die for
at your age?

1054
01:27:42,150 --> 01:27:44,090
Because life is hard.

1055
01:27:59,670 --> 01:28:00,900
Here, drink up.

1056
01:28:02,370 --> 01:28:06,970
Now, tell me.
Why did you do that?

1057
01:28:07,840 --> 01:28:09,570
Because I am ugly.

1058
01:28:10,850 --> 01:28:12,780
Really, that's it?

1059
01:28:17,050 --> 01:28:18,880
Take off those glasses.

1060
01:28:18,960 --> 01:28:19,580
Why?

1061
01:28:21,060 --> 01:28:22,080
Just do it.

1062
01:28:25,460 --> 01:28:26,290
Come here.

1063
01:28:28,460 --> 01:28:29,590
Let me see.

1064
01:28:40,340 --> 01:28:44,370
I see.
The glasses are great for you.

1065
01:28:45,950 --> 01:28:50,280
They cover up your flaws well.

1066
01:28:51,520 --> 01:28:54,180
I was just trying to hide
bags under my eyes.

1067
01:28:54,620 --> 01:28:57,790
You shouldn't be thinking about
killing yourself over nothing.

1068
01:29:01,700 --> 01:29:05,790
There's a Japanese writer,
Murakami Ryu said this once.

1069
01:29:05,870 --> 01:29:07,700
Sex over suicide...

1070
01:29:08,270 --> 01:29:10,000
I'm only in middle school.

1071
01:29:17,650 --> 01:29:18,480
Cheers.

1072
01:29:26,760 --> 01:29:30,280
Confess my love.
Don't confess.

1073
01:29:31,260 --> 01:29:33,990
Confess. Don't confess...

1074
01:29:50,350 --> 01:29:54,280
Go, Mr. Song. Go!

1075
01:30:56,950 --> 01:30:57,970
What is it?

1076
01:31:03,750 --> 01:31:04,380
Mom

1077
01:31:04,450 --> 01:31:05,280
Come over here.

1078
01:31:06,360 --> 01:31:07,880
What did he do to you?

1079
01:31:07,960 --> 01:31:08,980
Hey, Yeon-Joo

1080
01:31:10,960 --> 01:31:13,690
What'd you do to my daughter?

1081
01:31:13,760 --> 01:31:15,590
What the...

1082
01:31:23,070 --> 01:31:24,370
Ugh, my back.

1083
01:31:24,440 --> 01:31:26,470
No, Yeon-Joo.
Don't get me wrong.

1084
01:31:26,540 --> 01:31:27,770
What are you doing, mom?

1085
01:31:27,840 --> 01:31:31,580
No, it's not like that.
You got it wrong.

1086
01:31:35,250 --> 01:31:36,480
Open up!

1087
01:31:36,550 --> 01:31:38,880
- You're wrong.
- You're hurting me.

1088
01:31:40,320 --> 01:31:43,990
You're giving me a hard time.
You're wrong.

1089
01:31:45,760 --> 01:31:47,090
Ugh, my back.

1090
01:31:50,470 --> 01:31:52,490
Listen, there's a misunderstanding.

1091
01:31:52,570 --> 01:31:54,400
Let me explain.

1092
01:31:54,470 --> 01:31:57,000
I'm calling the cops.
You can explain it to them.

1093
01:31:57,070 --> 01:31:58,170
Why are you calling the cops?

1094
01:31:58,840 --> 01:31:59,670
Why not?

1095
01:31:59,740 --> 01:32:01,180
- Don't call the cops.
- Why not?

1096
01:32:01,240 --> 01:32:02,470
- Just don't!
- Why?

1097
01:32:02,550 --> 01:32:05,780
Don't, don't. Just don't!

1098
01:32:09,250 --> 01:32:12,880
Friggin... argh!

1099
01:32:16,690 --> 01:32:18,790
How could you do that
to a little girl?

1100
01:32:18,860 --> 01:32:19,890
- Do what?
- It's not like that, mom.

1101
01:32:19,960 --> 01:32:20,790
You just stand back.

1102
01:32:20,860 --> 01:32:24,300
Hey, you're a real piece of work.

1103
01:32:24,370 --> 01:32:27,000
Your kid is having
a life or death situation,

1104
01:32:27,070 --> 01:32:29,700
Yet, here you are passed out drunk.

1105
01:32:29,770 --> 01:32:33,070
And what do you do?
Wrongfully accuse me?

1106
01:32:33,940 --> 01:32:37,170
What do you mean she was dying?

1107
01:32:37,250 --> 01:32:41,580
She tried to kill herself.
You daughter, Seong-Hwa. Okay?

1108
01:32:41,650 --> 01:32:43,590
It's not Seong-Hwa.
It's Seong-Ah!

1109
01:32:47,860 --> 01:32:49,790
Why would you want to kill youself?

1110
01:32:49,860 --> 01:32:54,090
What is he talking about?
Tell me he's lying.

1111
01:32:54,760 --> 01:32:57,100
Why do you care if I live or die?

1112
01:32:58,170 --> 01:33:00,500
You already wish I were never born.

1113
01:33:03,470 --> 01:33:05,870
How could you tell her that?

1114
01:33:05,940 --> 01:33:07,170
You did.

1115
01:33:07,580 --> 01:33:09,370
When you got drunk
and had a fight with dad!

1116
01:33:09,450 --> 01:33:15,280
Come on, Seong-Ah.
You know I'm not well.

1117
01:33:15,350 --> 01:33:18,290
What are you,
blame it on the depression?

1118
01:33:18,850 --> 01:33:22,980
Do you know
why you're depressed?

1119
01:33:23,060 --> 01:33:24,890
It's because your body
isn't busy enough.

1120
01:33:25,060 --> 01:33:27,690
Women today don't do anything.

1121
01:33:29,030 --> 01:33:35,400
Your depression could be cured
by working out every morning.

1122
01:33:35,470 --> 01:33:36,500
Don't get smart with me.

1123
01:33:36,570 --> 01:33:39,170
Really, I'm sick of your family.

1124
01:33:40,140 --> 01:33:43,870
Your husband, Gi-Soo Hahm.

1125
01:33:44,750 --> 01:33:46,080
Didn't he kill himself too?

1126
01:33:47,250 --> 01:33:50,980
He didn't want to live with you.

1127
01:33:51,050 --> 01:33:53,280
So, he fell off the roof.

1128
01:33:53,360 --> 01:33:55,880
Good job, Gi-Soo Hahm.

1129
01:33:59,630 --> 01:34:01,320
How'd you know?

1130
01:34:01,400 --> 01:34:02,190
What?

1131
01:34:02,970 --> 01:34:05,700
That my husband fell to death.

1132
01:34:06,370 --> 01:34:08,000
You told me.

1133
01:34:08,870 --> 01:34:09,800
No, I didn't.

1134
01:34:11,740 --> 01:34:13,370
How'd you know his name?

1135
01:34:16,450 --> 01:34:17,380
You.

1136
01:34:20,350 --> 01:34:22,370
You killed my husband.

1137
01:34:23,450 --> 01:34:25,390
No, no!

1138
01:34:25,450 --> 01:34:27,680
I didn't do it.

1139
01:34:27,760 --> 01:34:30,390
Come on, just hear me out.
Stay still.

1140
01:34:30,460 --> 01:34:31,980
You're hurting your kid...

1141
01:34:32,060 --> 01:34:32,890
- Go away.
- I will explain everything.

1142
01:34:32,960 --> 01:34:35,400
Stop throwing things.

1143
01:34:35,460 --> 01:34:38,090
Calm down.
I will explain everything.

1144
01:34:38,170 --> 01:34:41,400
Don't! I am sick!

1145
01:34:41,470 --> 01:34:42,700
What are you doing in my house?

1146
01:34:42,770 --> 01:34:44,470
Stop throwing things.

1147
01:34:44,540 --> 01:34:47,870
Look at me. I'm hurting right now.
Let me explain.

1148
01:34:47,940 --> 01:34:50,470
Why am I here?

1149
01:34:50,550 --> 01:34:51,980
Well, because I am a writer.
I'm here to write.

1150
01:34:52,050 --> 01:34:54,380
You must have a reason
for coming here!

1151
01:34:56,250 --> 01:34:57,580
You really want to hear it out?

1152
01:34:59,160 --> 01:35:03,250
Okay, do you know of
the Blue Dragon Tea Cup?

1153
01:35:03,330 --> 01:35:04,790
It's a tea cup this small.

1154
01:35:06,960 --> 01:35:07,790
I don't know
what you're talking about...

1155
01:35:07,860 --> 01:35:09,390
I think you do.

1156
01:35:09,470 --> 01:35:11,990
Don't Don't!

1157
01:35:12,070 --> 01:35:12,500
- Well...
- Don't.

1158
01:35:12,570 --> 01:35:13,590
Get the hell out of my house.

1159
01:35:13,670 --> 01:35:17,260
Your husband told me.
He hid it in this house somewhere.

1160
01:35:17,340 --> 01:35:18,970
As soon as I get my hands on it,

1161
01:35:19,040 --> 01:35:23,070
I will leave your house,
even if you tell me not to.

1162
01:35:23,150 --> 01:35:25,880
I really don't know anything about it.

1163
01:35:25,950 --> 01:35:28,680
It's 2 million dollars. Two!

1164
01:35:29,890 --> 01:35:31,380
Mom, let's find it.

1165
01:35:31,450 --> 01:35:33,890
With that money,
the store will be okay.

1166
01:35:33,960 --> 01:35:35,980
The mortgage will be paid for, too.

1167
01:35:36,060 --> 01:35:38,580
And I can afford my cosmetic surgery.

1168
01:35:39,860 --> 01:35:42,090
Nothing to lose, mom.

1169
01:35:49,070 --> 01:35:52,870
Yes, we're keeping on eye on him.

1170
01:36:05,350 --> 01:36:06,380
Over there, get him!

1171
01:36:15,230 --> 01:36:16,390
Get in, you idiots!

1172
01:36:30,850 --> 01:36:31,870
Get closer. Come on!

1173
01:36:36,850 --> 01:36:38,480
Hurry!

1174
01:37:21,060 --> 01:37:21,890
Turn around!

1175
01:38:04,140 --> 01:38:05,470
Hey you!

1176
01:38:16,950 --> 01:38:17,980
You jerk!

1177
01:38:22,060 --> 01:38:23,990
Let go of me!

1178
01:38:24,860 --> 01:38:27,090
Let go of me. Let go!

1179
01:38:31,470 --> 01:38:33,200
Hey hey! Get in!

1180
01:38:34,200 --> 01:38:36,300
Come back here, punk!

1181
01:38:42,080 --> 01:38:45,480
So this is the Blue Dragon Tea Cup?

1182
01:38:45,550 --> 01:38:48,280
Can we repair it?

1183
01:38:48,350 --> 01:38:49,080
No, we can't.

1184
01:38:49,150 --> 01:38:53,090
Can we get something
similar looking?

1185
01:38:53,160 --> 01:38:54,590
We can't get something like this.

1186
01:38:54,660 --> 01:38:58,390
It will have to be of a certain class
to look like a $10 million piece.

1187
01:39:01,800 --> 01:39:05,200
I believe Mr. Song
took the company car out.

1188
01:39:05,270 --> 01:39:06,200
What about it?

1189
01:39:06,670 --> 01:39:10,970
We have dozens of eye witnesses
and a security camera.

1190
01:39:12,270 --> 01:39:13,470
Security camera.

1191
01:39:14,310 --> 01:39:16,610
What shall we do now?

1192
01:39:16,680 --> 01:39:18,480
You know I'm frigid.

1193
01:39:18,550 --> 01:39:19,570
Mr. Cho!

1194
01:39:20,750 --> 01:39:22,980
Well, we can report a stolen vehicle

1195
01:39:23,050 --> 01:39:25,080
and make sure Mr. Song
doesn't come near the company.

1196
01:39:25,150 --> 01:39:26,680
Can't get too wrong from here.

1197
01:39:26,760 --> 01:39:28,690
Okay, then don't let him near here.

1198
01:39:30,760 --> 01:39:34,890
Then you told me not to let
Mr. Song come to work.

1199
01:39:34,960 --> 01:39:36,690
Mr. Song, Mr. Schmong.

1200
01:39:36,770 --> 01:39:39,100
I need to figure out
what to report to my father.

1201
01:39:39,170 --> 01:39:40,800
Can we draw up some paper work?

1202
01:39:40,870 --> 01:39:42,390
You mean, fix the book?

1203
01:39:42,470 --> 01:39:45,070
Yeah, let's give accounting
100~200 grand and go from there.

1204
01:39:46,440 --> 01:39:48,570
Then, let me fire Mr. Song first,

1205
01:39:48,640 --> 01:39:51,480
and I'll look into accounting.

1206
01:39:53,450 --> 01:39:58,180
Is there really no way
to repair this?

1207
01:40:06,460 --> 01:40:09,800
Now, no one will be interested
in your house.

1208
01:40:09,870 --> 01:40:12,800
No matter how long it takes,
go through every inch of your place.

1209
01:40:14,240 --> 01:40:17,870
I'm going into hiding for a while.
Call me as soon as you find it.

1210
01:40:19,540 --> 01:40:22,480
Go into hiding, why?

1211
01:40:22,540 --> 01:40:25,270
Do I really have
to explain that to you?

1212
01:40:25,350 --> 01:40:26,970
Don't yell at me!

1213
01:40:27,350 --> 01:40:29,480
Walk me through it, step by step.

1214
01:40:38,960 --> 01:40:40,490
Okay, missus.

1215
01:40:40,560 --> 01:40:43,590
I have to hide out,

1216
01:40:43,670 --> 01:40:45,690
because I am wanted.

1217
01:40:46,570 --> 01:40:48,400
Does that make sense, missus?

1218
01:40:49,370 --> 01:40:52,270
Pull yourself together.
It's 2 million we're talking here.

1219
01:40:52,840 --> 01:40:55,570
Without me, you can't even sell this.

1220
01:40:55,640 --> 01:40:59,170
Don't let others take it
away from you.

1221
01:40:59,250 --> 01:41:01,270
Stay focused!

1222
01:41:05,050 --> 01:41:05,880
I'll be going now.

1223
01:41:14,260 --> 01:41:15,090
Hey

1224
01:41:16,370 --> 01:41:17,590
What about my car?

1225
01:41:17,670 --> 01:41:19,900
Seriously,
you're worried about your car?

1226
01:41:21,470 --> 01:41:24,960
You really annoy me, you know that?

1227
01:42:03,550 --> 01:42:05,380
He was transferred to holdings,
yesterday.

1228
01:42:05,450 --> 01:42:08,910
So he wasn't really a writer?

1229
01:42:08,980 --> 01:42:11,680
He was a cultural property smuggler.
With a long list of priors.

1230
01:42:13,020 --> 01:42:15,680
I know I called you
out of suspicion,

1231
01:42:16,560 --> 01:42:17,990
But I never thought...

1232
01:42:20,060 --> 01:42:22,500
- What if he...
- Don't you worry.

1233
01:42:22,560 --> 01:42:25,000
He's going to think
he got real unlucky and got caught.

1234
01:42:25,070 --> 01:42:27,190
He will never suspect you
for turning him in.

1235
01:42:27,270 --> 01:42:29,900
I did some thinking myself.

1236
01:42:31,910 --> 01:42:33,970
Thank you for everything.

1237
01:42:34,040 --> 01:42:36,770
Could I have a cup of coffee?

1238
01:42:36,850 --> 01:42:38,780
We don't drink coffee.

1239
01:42:38,850 --> 01:42:40,180
Oh, Okay.

1240
01:42:48,160 --> 01:42:51,680
Did he say anything else?

1241
01:42:51,760 --> 01:42:53,190
Like what?

1242
01:42:55,060 --> 01:42:57,190
It's nothing. Never mind.

1243
01:43:04,240 --> 01:43:05,760
You want us to do all of this?

1244
01:43:05,840 --> 01:43:07,570
What are you saying?

1245
01:43:08,040 --> 01:43:11,380
All of these are ours.
Your dads, okay?

1246
01:43:12,250 --> 01:43:13,870
Come on. Give me a hand.

1247
01:44:49,650 --> 01:44:50,580
It's cold.

1248
01:45:21,980 --> 01:45:22,910
Seong-Ah, don't come out.

1249
01:45:48,440 --> 01:45:50,670
I was a gentleman to you two.

1250
01:45:51,740 --> 01:45:54,970
Out of respect to your husband,
I offered to split it 50:50.

1251
01:45:55,040 --> 01:45:56,070
I'm really sorry.

1252
01:45:56,950 --> 01:45:58,170
By the way, you must know,

1253
01:45:58,950 --> 01:46:01,180
There are security cameras everywhere.

1254
01:46:02,250 --> 01:46:03,680
You were filmed on your way in,

1255
01:46:03,750 --> 01:46:07,090
down the hallway, in the elevator.

1256
01:46:07,160 --> 01:46:08,180
Do you think I care?

1257
01:46:08,260 --> 01:46:16,100
Those few minutes on your security feed
isn't going to stop me.

1258
01:46:20,870 --> 01:46:24,570
Nice digs!

1259
01:46:28,340 --> 01:46:29,280
You got here.

1260
01:46:35,450 --> 01:46:36,580
2 million, my ass.

1261
01:46:37,550 --> 01:46:39,080
I got exactly 200 grand.

1262
01:46:40,060 --> 01:46:42,080
I know you have a million left,

1263
01:46:44,260 --> 01:46:45,780
So don't even think about it.

1264
01:47:11,850 --> 01:47:14,690
What's wrong?
When did this begin?

1265
01:47:17,160 --> 01:47:19,290
I haven't been able to sleep.

1266
01:47:20,760 --> 01:47:24,600
I haven't slept all week.

1267
01:47:26,370 --> 01:47:29,200
I think I'll be fine if I can sleep,

1268
01:47:30,940 --> 01:47:33,570
But I feel awful.

1269
01:47:35,040 --> 01:47:38,770
My life sucks.

1270
01:47:48,960 --> 01:47:52,980
I know how you feel.

1271
01:47:56,970 --> 01:47:59,700
Do you sleep alright now?

1272
01:48:02,570 --> 01:48:04,060
Yes, I sleep just fine.

1273
01:48:07,640 --> 01:48:09,270
I don't even take pills anymore.

1274
01:48:10,650 --> 01:48:14,580
Bitch, you got better alone.

1275
01:48:17,050 --> 01:48:18,680
Can I get a drink?

1276
01:48:19,450 --> 01:48:21,080
I quit drinking.

1277
01:48:23,160 --> 01:48:26,490
Not fair. Really, not funny.

1278
01:48:28,760 --> 01:48:30,700
I'm doing okay for now,

1279
01:48:32,170 --> 01:48:34,190
But who knows?

1280
01:48:37,740 --> 01:48:40,170
I'm sorry for hitting you earlier.

1281
01:48:42,540 --> 01:48:44,380
We can call it even
on the china price.

1282
01:48:45,850 --> 01:48:47,970
What china price are we even on?

1283
01:48:48,850 --> 01:48:51,580
Look at you, so coy.

1284
01:48:53,050 --> 01:48:54,890
As soon as the bank opens
tomorrow morning,

1285
01:48:54,960 --> 01:48:57,080
we're going together
to get my money.

1286
01:49:06,570 --> 01:49:08,500
I'm going to lie down here.

1287
01:49:13,240 --> 01:49:16,870
I can't move an inch.

1288
01:49:25,350 --> 01:49:27,580
Are you hungry?
What do you want?

1289
01:49:29,260 --> 01:49:33,390
Your surgery went well, huh?

1290
01:49:34,260 --> 01:49:36,200
Not really.

1291
01:49:36,260 --> 01:49:38,820
It's going to be fine,
once it settles in.

1292
01:49:38,900 --> 01:49:41,200
It's all settled in already.

1293
01:49:45,770 --> 01:49:50,800
Well, the sun will
come out again some day.

1294
01:49:50,880 --> 01:49:52,680
It's just life.

1295
01:50:23,450 --> 01:50:26,070
Warm milk will help you
fall asleep.

1296
01:50:26,150 --> 01:50:29,880
Damn, I had just fallen asleep.

1297
01:50:40,960 --> 01:50:42,590
Man, it's loud in here.

1298
01:50:50,170 --> 01:50:53,870
So, is he going to
move in with us now?

1299
01:50:54,740 --> 01:50:55,270
What?

1300
01:50:55,940 --> 01:50:57,880
You know,
we have to split it in half,

1301
01:50:58,450 --> 01:51:00,280
And we don't have a room to spare.

1302
01:51:01,150 --> 01:51:07,280
Why don't you let me
